# Zustand Patterns

## Selectors: Always Use Individual Selectors

Never destructure the entire store — it subscribes to all state and causes unnecessary re-renders.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — re-renders on ANY store change
const { parseResult, expandedNodes, toggleNode } = useJsonStore()

// ✅ GOOD — re-renders only when specific values change
const parseResult = useJsonStore((s) => s.parseResult)
const expandedNodes = useJsonStore((s) => s.expandedNodes)
const toggleNode = useJsonStore((s) => s.toggleNode)
```

Actions (functions) are stable references in Zustand 5 and never trigger re-renders.

## Multi-Value Selectors: Use useShallow

When you need multiple state values together, use `useShallow` to avoid re-renders from new object references:

```typescript
import { useShallow } from 'zustand/react/shallow'

const { matchIds, activeMatchIndex } = useSearchStore(
  useShallow((s) => ({ matchIds: s.matchIds, activeMatchIndex: s.activeMatchIndex }))
)
```

## Batch State Updates

Never call state-mutating actions in a loop. Add batch actions instead:

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — N state updates, N re-renders
matches.forEach((id) => expandToNode(id))

// ✅ GOOD — single state update
expandNodes(matches)
```

## Testing Stores

Use `getInitialState()` for clean resets in tests:

```typescript
afterEach(() => {
  useJsonStore.setState(useJsonStore.getInitialState(), true)
})
```
